body:
the REAL Emmy winners p2

The shitstorm: Sandra will be last because I HAVE A LOT TO SAY about that.

Betty Gilpin: supporting actress in a comedy - simply put GLOW is one of if not the best show on Netflix. Gilpin’s work is crucial to that. Her character arcs are beautiful and honestly the fact Allison Brie was not also nominated is a travesty.

Any of the Atlanta episodes: comedy writing and directing - DEAR JESUS EMMYS ARE YOU STUPID! Listen watch the damn episodes and they speak for themselves. Haunting and wonderful and beautiful at every turn. The writing is extraordinary and should have been honored.

I’m not even going to acknowledge the supporting actor in a drama category cause it’s a bore and probably should have gone to David Harbour if it was going to be any of those white men.

Brandon Victor Dixon: supporting actor in a limited series - Judas is such a demanding role and must be done correctly in order for Jesus Christ Superstar to work and by god does he do a phenomenal job. Too bad the emmys have a western hard-on.

Letitia Wright: supporting actress in a limited series - how? Just how? I thought this was a gimme. Oh Jesus, her performance is OUTSTANDING and should have been recognized.

I HAVE A THING ABOUT BATHROOMS: writing for a drama - my problem isn’t that The Americans boyz won, it’s that the wrong episode of killing eve was nominated in the first place. Let us all remember the table scene was just offhandedly written by Phoebe and remained practically the same in the final script. I don’t have words for just how sensational that whole scene is and the episode as a whole is. Every emotion is hit and it sets up the back half of the series without being boring.

And the moment you’ve all been waiting for:

SANDRA MOTHERFUCKING OH: Killing Eve is made by the performance of its two leads. Sandra Oh’s ability as an actress can not entirely be put into words. This show falls apart without her. She every episode raises her game and forces the people around her to do the same. I’m also going to make the argument Jodie should have been nominated as well because their performances hinge on the other. One can not truly be great without the other. To only nominate one only gives part of the show. The two together create the masterpiece that is killing eve. Take Elizabeth Moss out simple. Eve Polastri is a character all people can relate to in some form, thanks to Sandra Oh. Her slow descent is portrayed carefully and delicately by Oh and no one besides Keri Russell could make the argument she does it better. There is not doubt in my mind she deserved that award.

Also fuck got winning for best drama, The Americans deserved to win and you fucks know it.

Thank you for listening to my TED talk, see you soon pals.

summary: Fans left disappointed after Killing Eve star Sandra Oh misses out on Emmy!
title: Fans left disappointed after Killing Eve star Sandra Oh misses out on Emmy!
body:
Fans left disappointed after Killing Eve star Sandra Oh misses out on Emmy!

Fans took to Twitter to express their disappointment that Killing Eve star Sandra Oh missed out on an Emmy to The Crown’s Claire Foy.

Oh made history when she became the first actress of Asian descent to be nominated for lead actress in a drama series for her role in the BBC America show, in which she plays an MI5 officer who is chasing an assassin.

However the gong went to British actress Foy,…
